Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/schematron.c
+++ b/schematron.c
@@ -1454,7 +1454,13 @@
             comp = xmlXPathCtxtCompile(ctxt->xctxt, select);
-            eval = xmlXPathCompiledEval(comp, ctxt->xctxt);
-
-            switch (eval->type) {
+            eval = xmlXPathCompiledEval(comp, ctxt->xctxt);
+            if (eval == NULL) {
+                /* Could not evaluate XPath expression, skip this child */
+                if (select != NULL)
+                    xmlFree(select);
+                continue;
+            }
+
+            switch (eval->type) {
'}`
responded: The root cause of the null dereference is that `xmlXPathCompiledEval` can return `NULL`, but the code immediately dereferences `eval` (at `switch (eval->type)`) without checking if it is `NULL`. To fix this, we need to add a check after the call to `xmlXPathCompiledEval` to ensure `eval` is not `NULL` before dereferencing it. If it is `NULL`, we should skip the switch and possibly handle the error gracefully.

I will now generate a patch to add this check.

